<HEADLINE> Istanbul Stock Exchange Index Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Istanbul Stock
Exchange National-100 Index closed at 2,640.19 points on Monday,
up 2.47 points, or 0.15 percent, from last Friday's finish.
</P>
<P>
The trading was heavy with the turnover reaching 55 trillion
Turkish Liras (over 198 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The industrial index went up 3.10 points, or 0.27 percent, to
close at 2,166.50 points, and the service index rose 20.92
points, or 0.68 percent, to close at 3,304.80 points, while the
financial index went down 7.39 points, or 0.16 percent, to close
at 3,278.03 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
