<HEADLINE> Sino-U.S. Volunteer Program Under Way in Shaanxi Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 400 teachers and
students from 12 private schools in Shaanxi Province warmly
welcomed a group of newly arrived U.S. volunteers here today.
</P>
<P>
A congratulatory letter from U.S. President Bill Clinton was
read at the session, expressing his determination to create a
brighter future and improve mutual understanding with younger
generations.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. volunteers are participating in an international
cultural exchange project which was launched in April of 1996.
</P>
<P>
As of August, 259 U.S. volunteers were participating in the
program in Shaanxi Province. The project gained maturity after the
signing of the Sino-U.S. Joint Declaration when Clinton was in
China this summer.  
</P>
</TEXT>
