<DOCNO> XIE19980908.0004 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan on U.N. War Against Poverty  (Embargoed for Tuesday) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Despite its limited
resources, the United Nations "has made the eradication of poverty
a central cross-cutting goal of its activities," U.N.
Secretary-General Kofi Annan said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In his annual report to the 52nd session of the General
Assembly, Annan said, "Guided by the outcomes of its major world
conferences of the 1990s, especially the 1995 World Summit for
Social Development, the United Nations has made the eradication of
poverty a central cross-cutting goal of its activities."
</P>
<P>
To meet the main purpose of the anti-poverty drive, the
185-member world body has adopted a plan to "seek better
coordination and greater cooperation between the various elements
of the United Nations system, including the Bretton Woods
institutions, and to agree on a shared strategy addressing all of
the key dimensions of action against poverty" he said.
</P>
<P>
The Bretton Woods institutions resulted from a July 1944
meeting held at the Bretton Woods on the invitation of the United
States. The meeting led to the creation of the two post-war
international financial institutions, namely the International
Monetary Fund (IMF) and the International Bank for Reconstruction
and Development. The latter has been popularly known as the World
Bank.
</P>
<P>
"During the past year, the United Nations assisted some 100
countries with the preparation, formulation or implementation of
national anti-poverty programs," he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the U.N. chief listed some areas which have to be
improved in order to broaden the scope of action against poverty:
to address such critical issues as access to productive assets; to
encourage a more inclusive dialogue between the State, civil
society and the private sector; and to target resource-poor
communities and asset-poor households.
</P>
<P>
"A substantial share of UNDP resources -- some 26 percent of
the total -- is now devoted directly to poverty reduction," he
said.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations Development Program (UNDP) renders
assistance in such fields as support for poverty mapping,
assessments of national capacity for poverty reduction, setting
national goals and targets, public expenditure reviews, review of
policies, administrative structure and procedures, and resource
mobilization.
</P>
<P>
"Achieving the eradication of poverty also requires that the
feminization of poverty be reversed," Annan said, adding that this
is because "poverty is a major cause of hunger, but hunger also
causes and perpetuates inter-generational cycles of poverty."
</P>
<P>
In his report, Annan also spoke highly of the efforts by the
World Food Program to carry out "vulnerability assessment mapping"
in 22 African, 8 Asian and 2 Latin American countries.
</P>
<P>
"This exercise identifies the geographic distribution of
poverty and food insecurity, and helps ascertain their underlying
causes together with the approaching programmatic responses,"
Annan added.
</P>
<P>
To ensure that the poor have sustained access to food, the
World Food Program targets some 60 percent of its development
resources directly to women and involves them in the management of
food distribution and in decision-making.
</P>
<P>
The 52nd session of the U.N. General Assembly is expected to
consider and approve the annual report before its conclusion on
Tuesday. It will be followed by the 53rd session of the General
Assembly, which begins one week earlier than usual.
</P>
<P>
The General Assembly, the main deliberation organ, is composed
of representatives of all 185 U.N. members. The General Assembly's
regular session used to begin each year on the third Tuesday in
September and continues usually until mid-December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
