<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Postpones Visit to Kazakhstan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris
Yeltsin has postponed his visit to Kazakhstan from September 8-9
to October 12-13, his press office announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made due to the political situation in Russia,
the office said.
</P>
<P>
Kazakh President Nursultan Nazarbayev expressed his
understanding in a telephone conversation with Yeltsin, said the
press office.
</P>
<P>
The State Duma, or lower house of parliament, again rejected
Viktor Chernomyrdin's nomination as prime minister in a second
voting Monday. Chernomyrdin was first rejected last Monday by the
Duma, but he was renominated by Yeltsin. No date has been set so
far for the third or final voting. 
</P>
