<HEADLINE> Pak Cabinet Decides to Discuss Signing of CTBT </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's federal cabinet
has decided to discuss the issue of signing the Comprehensive Test
Ban Treaty (CTBT) in the parliament and final decision in this
regard would be taken on the basis of national consensus in
supreme national interest, a senior minister said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The Cabinet has decided to hold a full fledged and
comprehensive debate on the question of CTBT and decision will be
taken on the basis of national consensus," Information Minister
Mushahid Hussain told reporters during a press briefing at
Parliament House Monday.
</P>
<P>
He said the decision on the question of the CTBT would be taken
in supreme national interest and would not be taken under coercion
of sanctions or economic pressure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
