<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- Cambodian police Monday opened fire at opposition
protesters outside the Cambodiana Hotel in the centre of the city,
killing at least one person and wounding many others.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of policemen armed with submachine guns opened fire
after they failed to disperse thousands of Sam Rainsy supporters
outside the hotel with batons. (Cambodia-Politics-Shooting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian State Duma again rejected Viktor
Chernomyrdin's nomination as prime minister on Monday, despite
earlier efforts to break the political stalemate.
</P>
<P>
Only 138 deputies at the lower house of parliament voted for
Chernomyrdin, who was renamed premier August 24 after five months
in the political wilderness, way below the required simple
majority of 226 votes. Two hundred and seventy-three deputies
voted against with one abstention. (Russia-Duma-Chernomyrdin)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PHNOM PENH -- The Sam Rainsy Party (SRP) launched a strong
protest on Monday afternoon at the government's decision to arrest
SRP leader Sam Rainsy.
</P>
<P>
A statement released by the SRP said that the SRP urgently
appeals to the Cambodian government to de-escalate the situation
for the sake of peace and democracy in Cambodia.
</P>
