JOHANNESBURG -- Seventeen people were killed and at least 80
others injured when a passenger bus collided with a truck in South
Africa's North-West Province Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
"We're still investigating the cause of the accident, but we
suspect that one of the vehicles veered out of its lane, resulting
in a head-on collision," said Louis Jacobs, a police spokesman.
(SAfrica-Accident Toll) 
