<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique Marks 24th Victory Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano, accompanied by leaders of the state government and
political parties, laid a wreath at the Monument to the People's
Heroes here to mark the 24th Victory Day Monday.
</P>
<P>
In his speech after the ceremony, Chissano called on all
Mozambicans to carry out the behest of the fallen heroes, and
work hard to rebuild the country, following the examples set by
those combatants fighting for the national independence.
</P>
<P>
Victory Day falls on September 7 each year when 24 years ago,
the Mozambique Liberation Front (Frelimo) signed a Lusaka
agreement with Lisbon on granting independence to Mozambique on
June 25, 1975.
</P>
<P>
The Central Committee of the ruling Frelimo in a message to
the whole nation Monday urged all political forces and
organizations to cherish the national unity and the ideal of
independence and freedom.
</P>
<P>
It called on all Mozambicans to take an active part in
promoting the development of both urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
The central committee also urged the government departments to
take effective measures to help rehabilitate women socially and
economically and support helpless children and old people.
</P>
<P>
The Association of Veterans for the National Liberation also
asked their members to set good examples for the younger
generations in loving peace, preserving national solidarity and
upholding freedom and sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
Victory Day was also celebrated in other parts of the country,
with songs and dances, sports games and fora. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
