<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 157 Aircraft Accidents Occurred in S. Africa Last </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 152 South
African registered aircraft were involved in accidents last year,
transport minister Mac Maharaj said Monday.
</P>
<P>
They include 21 fatal accidents, in which 37 people were
killed, he told the national council of provinces.
</P>
<P>
Maharaj said many of the accidents that occurred in 1997 were
still under investigation and the causes were not yet established
or could not yet be released.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, five non-fatal accidents to foreign
registered aircraft which occurred in South Africa were also
still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
