<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> G7 Meeting on Russia to be Held on September 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The British government
announced Monday that the Group of Seven (G7) industrial countries
would hold a scheduled meeting in London on September 12 to
discuss the worsening Russian financial situation.
</P>
<P>
A British Foreign Office spokesman was quoted by Reuters as
saying that all the G7 countries had already responded
positively to the invitation and the meeting was "almost 95
percent sure" to go ahead.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman confirmed that London meeting would be held at
deputy ministerial level and the International Monetary Fund,
World Bank and the European Commission would send their
representatives to the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The London meeting is expected to take stock of Russia's
deepening financial crisis and make various recommendations to G7
leaders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
