<HEADLINE> Romanian Currency Steadily Depreciates Compared to Dollar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Romania's currency went on
depreciating, and exceeded on Monday the ceiling of 9000 lei per
U.S. dollar by losing 18 units in only two days.
</P>
<P>
The exchange rate the Romanian Central Bank announced on Monday
was close to rates in exchange offices where a dollar was sold for
9006 lei and was bought for 8970 lei on average.
</P>
<P>
The Saturday announcement by the government of the intention to
increase duties and excises on tobacco and alcohol caused
immediately an unrest on the financial market and the occurrence of
the "emotional factor" phenomenon among people.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank governor Mugur Isarescu forecasted a
depreciation of 1-2 percent per month of the Romanian currency leu
against the dollar for the second half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Bucharest Stock Exchange (BVB) and the Rasdaq (the
secondary market) didn't register any spectacular evolutions on
Monday, maintaining a decreasing trend in transactions. The
transaction value lowered to 2.71 billion lei (301,000 U.S.
dollars) compared to 2.89 billion lei (321,000 U.S. dollars) on
Friday at the closing of the BVB's transaction session on Monday.
</P>
