nation's general elections.
</P>
<P>
"The elections offer a chance for Bosnia to overcome divisions
created by the war and to embrace modern European values," the
15-nation union said in a statement issued by its Austrian
presidency.
</P>
<P>
The European Union is ready to continue to help if the Bosnians
continue to take the responsibilities under the Dayton peace
accord to build up a peaceful, democratic, multi-ethnic and open
state, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The union described the September 12-13 elections as "a unique
opportunity" to stay on the path toward Bosnia's closer
integration into the European community.
</P>
<P>
"Seize this opportunity by choosing responsible leaders who
will manage the country's affairs honestly and will pursue the
future you want for yourselves and for your children," the
statement added.
</P>
<P>
But the European Union was dismayed by recent violence in
Bosnia and appealed to all parties concerned to stop such actions.
</P>
