<HEADLINE> Nigeria to Start Privatization Program Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA (Nigeria), September 7 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's
privatization and commercialization of major public enterprises
will begin soon with an enabling decree, military leader
Abdulsalam Abubakar said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar made the statement at a press conference in the
capital city of Abuja, which was the first time he was formally
addressing the international media since taking power three
months ago.
</P>
<P>
He said all illegal competition will be repealed to attract
foreign and domestic investment, adding that Nigeria will
entrench a transparent regulatory framework for competition and
non-discrimination in all sectors of economy before the end of
this year.
</P>
<P>
The framework, he said, will be transparent and based on
competitive bidding for equity stake and management control of
major public enterprises.
</P>
<P>
"We intend to partially privatize the major public enterprises
whose performances have had negative impact on the well-being and
economic growth of our nation," he said in a written statement.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar appealed to the international society to come and
take part in the privatization program and urged Nigeria's
creditors to understand its reforms and unique problems to grant
it debt relief. 
</P>
</TEXT>
