<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> British, Irish Leaders Welcome Real IRA Ceasefire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- British and Irish leaders on
Tuesday welcomed reports that the group responsible for the worst
atrocity in nearly 30 years in Northern Ireland had declared a
total ceasefire.
</P>
<P>
Earlier on Tuesday, the Real IRA, which admits it set the
Omagh bomb last month that killed 29 people, said it had declared
"complete cessation" of military activities from midnight on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
British Prime Minister Tony Blair welcomed the move but he
made it clear that both British and Irish governments remained
determined to track down the Omagh bombers.
</P>
<P>
"We will continue to pursue those responsible for Omagh,"
Blair said in a statement issued by Downing Street.
</P>
<P>
Irish Prime Minister Bertie Ahern also welcomed the Real IRA's
ceasefire announcement.
</P>
<P>
"On the basis that this statement is now fully in effect and
final, it represents both an important and positive development,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The first minister of the Northern Irish assembly, David
Trimble, made a cautious welcome, saying it did not detract from
the horror of the Omagh bombing.
</P>
<P>
"I am glad these people have come to their senses and realize
the futility of their actions," he said. "But that doesn't change
the enormity of what they have done and their culpability for it."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980908.0046 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Charity Federation Donates to Jiangxi Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The China Charity Federation
here today donated cash and materials valued at 76.6 million RMB
yuan to east China's Jiangxi Province, which has been ravaged by
severe flooding this summer.
</P>
<P>
Because of several period of heavy rain since last June, the
province has suffered great material losses, and nearly 1.6
million people have been displaced.
</P>
<P>
The largest charitable organization in China, the federation
has collected large amounts of cash and materials from both at
home and abroad by means of giving benefit performances and
through other channels.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two senior officials from a Swedish international
aid foundation are expected here tomorrow to distribute to flood
victims 9,000 kg of biscuits and medicine valued at 300,000 yuan.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
