<DOCNO> XIE19980908.0047 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Bank Injects 193 million dollars into Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank signed a 193
million U.S. dollar credit agreement with Vietnam on Tuesday to
support agriculture diversification, urban transportation and
higher education programs.
</P>
<P>
The document was signed by Le Duc Thuy, the deputy governor of
the State Bank of Vietnam, and the World Bank director for Vietnam
Andrew Steer.
</P>
<P>
The agriculture diversification project, to be financed by the
loan, is aimed at increasing Vietnam's agricultural output and
employment while protecting the environment in some of the
country's poorest regions.
</P>
<P>
Some 42.7 million dollars of the loan, under the agreement,
will be used to improve the efficiency and safety of the
transportation systems in Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh city's central
areas.
</P>
<P>
About 83.3 million dollars of the loan will go into the higher
education sector to make it capable of meeting the current and
future needs of socio-economic development.
</P>
<P>
With the signing of the agreement, World Bank investment in
Vietnam has grown to nearly 2.2 billion dollars, excluding
technical assistance loans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
