<HEADLINE> UEFA Bans Two Players for Five Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Two players have been handed
five game bans after being sent off in the latest round of
European soccer competititons, UEFA announced on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Alexandre Khatskevitch of Dynamo Kiev was suspended following
his red card during the teams' Champions' League qualifying match
on August 12.
</P>
<P>
Forel Balint of Romania's Otelul Galati got his ban for
gesturing at an opponent following his second yellow card in a
UEFA Cup qualifying round match against Vejle BK of Denmark on A
ugust 28.
</P>
<P>
Five players were given four match bans. They are Francesco
Colonnese of Inter Milan, Thomas Winkelhofer and Ronald Hemming
of SV Salzburg, Aarno Turpeinen of HJK Helsinki and Tumer Metin
of Samsunspor. 
