<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK to Hold Harborfront Carnival to Attract Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Seeking to promote the
tourism industry and win back visitors, the Hong Kong Tourist
Association (HKTA) announced here Tuesday that a month-long
carnival will be held in Hong Kong between October to November
this year.
</P>
<P>
Jointly organized by the HKTA and Metro Broadcast
Co. Ltd. (MBC), the City of Life -- Harbor Fun Carnival series of
events set for the Tamar site by Hong Kong's Victoria Harbor are
schemed to encourage local residents to participate in an
activity that will help promote to rejuvenate Hong Kong's tourism
industry.
</P>
<P>
The event will also help to make the best use of the
spectacular waterfront.
</P>
<P>
The day-time events will be free of charge while, depending on
the nature of the evening events, admission fees may be levied.
</P>
<P>
Among the confirmed programs are the Mid-Autumn Lantern
Festival celebrations on October 5, which will feature
demonstrations of traditional Chinese lantern-making skills,
Cantonese opera presented in English, performances of traditional
folk songs, a pop concert and a Halloween Masquerade.
</P>
<P>
Also listed will be a Big Bowl Feast, which features a special
traditional Chinese culinary delight common in the Hakka walled
villages in northern Hong Kong's "New Territories", and a Food
Corner highlighting Hong Kong as the Culinary Heart of Asia and
offering plenty of choices including local-style and Chinese
regional cuisines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
