and their cooperation with Chinese large and medium-sized
businesses.
</P>
<P>
She said this in a speech at a symposium on the investment
strategy of multinational corporations which opened here
today.
</P>
<P>
She continued that multinational corporations play an important
role in global economic development.
</P>
<P>
With funds, management experience and practical technology from
the corporations, Chinese businesses will stand together with the
corporations to contribute to world economic development, Wu noted
in her speech on the theme of "The Asian financial crisis and
China's economic development."
</P>
<P>
"China will not falter in its efforts at modernization
construction despite the impact of the Asian financial crisis," Wu
said. She noted that the Chinese government is confident about
overcoming the difficulties caused by the crisis and that it can
keep stable its foreign economy and trade development.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the U.N. Conference on Trade and
Development (UNCTAD), the World Bank and some multinational
corporations attending the symposium also gave speeches on topics
including the effects of the Asian financial crisis and the
investment strategy of multinational corporations.
</P>
<P>
Rubens Ricupero, secretary-general of UNCTAD, said that China
has experienced a prosperous era in the field of direct overseas
investment over the past six years.
</P>
<P>
Last year, he added, the country attracted a total of 45
billion U.S. dollars in overseas investment, accounting for over
50 percent of the total in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The sound economic situation in China is what keeps the country
attractive to overseas investors, Ricupero said, adding that
China's infrastructure development and the opening up of some
service sectors will also help it attract more overseas funds.
</P>
