<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- A serious food crisis is
looming over Kinshasa, capital of the Democratic Republic of Congo
(DRC), a report reaching here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
More than five million residents in the capital are facing a
potentially explosive food crisis with the month-long civil war
blocking port supplies, diplomats and relief workers were quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
They said the stocks of food and chemicals for water treatment
in Kinshasa are only enough for four days' use at most.
</P>
<P>
And the power supply was disrupted by the rebels, leading to
further shortage of the city's water distribution.
</P>
<P>
The situation remains tense as the regional summit at Victoria
Falls of Zimbabwe Tuesday failed to reach a cease-fire with the
Congo rebels vowing to fight on.
</P>
<P>
European diplomats said Congolese President Laurent Kabila's
government had asked the West to help open an emergency air
corridor to supply Kinshasa with food, but there is no sign that
authorities can guarantee the safety of planes. 
</P>
