<HEADLINE> Technology Helps Chinese Farmers Get Affluent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Use one spade and one
pickaxe, and do all the farm work, Chinese farmers have been
working like this for thousands of years. But now they are turning
to farming technology which brings great changes in their lives.
</P>
<P>
More and more Chinese farmers come to realize that simple farm
tools are not enough and farming technology can lead them to
wealth.
</P>
<P>
Yu Wencang, a villager in Wuyi County in North China's Hebei
Province, turned to raise rabbits ten years ago. Because knowing
little of technology in stock farming, he failed.
</P>
<P>
After being trained in a technology school, he succeeded in
establishing a farm to raise rabbits and then he contracted
to run a farm to grow vegetables.
</P>
<P>
"It is farming technology that helped me get affluent," he
said, "I hope my fellow villagers will know more about it."
</P>
<P>
Yu has aided ten youngsters to have training class in a farming
technology school with a total of 20,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
To date, about three million farmers have become farming
technicians in various fields including agriculture, forestry,
animal husbandry and fishery, said an official from Chinese
Ministry of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
Liu Chuntai, a senior agronomist in Hebei, said that more and
more Chinese farmers became to realize the importance of science
and technology, and they are no longer satisfied with simple farm
tools.
</P>
<P>
Some farmers go to school to learn farming technology, and some
others join in various farming technology associations. A total of
240,000 farmers in Hebei have been members of these associations.
</P>
<P>
Farmers also invent new technology. A large number of new
technologies are invented by farmers every year, bringing about
wealth valued several billion yuan, said an official from the
Ministry of Agriculture.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
