</P>
<P>
Luoshan, 33.21 m, 1.71 m higher than the danger level.
</P>
<P>
Hankou, 28.25 m, 1.95 m higher.
</P>
<P>
Jiujiang, 21.97 m, 2.47 m higher.
</P>
<P>
Datong, 15.39 m, 0.89 meter higher.
</P>
<P>
Dongting Lake, 34.13 m, 2.13 m higher.
</P>
<P>
Poyang Lake, 21.39 m, 2.39 m higher.
</P>
<P>
Nanjing, 9.71 m, 1.21 m higher (at 11:30 today).
</P>
<P>
The water level of the mainstream of the Songhua River in
northeast China is still high, with the water level along the
Harbin section reported at 119.46 m at 14:00 today, 1.36 m higher
than the danger level, and in the Jiamusi section, 79.41 m, 0.41 m
higher than the danger level.
</P>
<P>
People combating flooding along the river dykes overcame six
crises yesterday, according to the report.  
