</P>
<P>
"We have sufficient stock of food and donors have committed
more food aid for the flood victims," Kibria told reporters at a
press conference on the flood situation in the country.
</P>
<P>
Denying mismanagement in the distribution of relief materials,
he said the government was following the time-tested method of
relief distribution.
</P>
<P>
The opposition, which has repeatedly accused the government of
mismanaging relief materials, called for an "All-party Flood
Relief Committee" last month, a proposal the government has
declined.
</P>
<P>
The people were suffering immensely in the longest flood in the
country, but they were not without food because food had been
reaching them adequately, the finance minister said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that as the flood situation continued to deteriorate
in the country, the exact extent of damage to property and crops
could not be ascertained at present.
</P>
<P>
The government had sought 879.5 million U.S. dollars in cash
and kind to take up emergency relief and post-flood and
rehabilitation work, and had received positive response from many
countries and international agencies, according to Kibria.
</P>
<P>
Highlighting the special steps taken by the government to
provide succor to the affected people, he said the government
would give Vulnerable Group Feeding (VGF) cards to about 250,000
flood-affected families, and 100,700 tons of rice had been
allocated for distribution under the VGF cards program.
</P>
<P>
"We will distribute 1,000 VGF cards in each union (township) of
the worst affected thanas (town), in the less affected unions 700,
500 and 300 cards will be distributed respectively considering the
extent of damage," he said.
</P>
<P>
The VGF program would be implemented for the next three months,
under which each card holder would get 16 kilograms of rice a
month as relief, according to the finance minister.
</P>
<P>
The country has 4,451 unions in 490 thanas, under 64 districts.
Forty-five districts have been hit by the ongoing devastating
flood since July, which has affected nearly 30 million people,
left more than 600 dead, and inflicted heavy losses in property
and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The government had decided to give 32.5 billion taka (691.5
million U.S. dollars) as agricultural loans, and a total of 120
million taka (2.56 million dollars) would be spent as house
building assistance, he added.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the press conference, David Lockwood, the resident
representative of the United Nations Development Program (UNDP),
said that the UNDP had received commitment of over 100 million
dollars against its "flash appeal" from the donor countries for
233 million dollars for flood-affected Bangladesh.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a ship carrying 15,000 tons of wheat for the World
Food Program (WFP), which has committed 228,000 tons of foodgrain
to Bangladesh, was heading for the country as emergency food
assistance, a WFP press release said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The ship originally carrying the wheat for another country was
now off the coast of Africa and would arrive in Bangladesh's
southeastern seaport of Chittagong by September 16, the release
said.
</P>
<P>
The wheat would be enough to provide one-month basic relief
food for over 900,000 destitute families though the VGF program,
it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
