<HEADLINE> Trade Fair Closes in Urumqi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Seventh Urumqi Economic and
Trade Fair, which closed today in this capital city of the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, chalked up transactions of 1.29
billion US dollars from overseas investors, and 7 billion RMB
yuan (about 846 million US dollars) from domestic investors.
</P>
<P>
The export contract value signed at the fair reached 510
million US dollars, and for the first time surpassed the import
value of 467 million US dollars, according to a local official.
</P>
<P>
