<HEADLINE> Former Sichuan Governor Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Lu Dadong, a former governor
of Sichuan province, died of illness at the age of 83 on August 28.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders including Jiang Zemin, Zhu Rongji, Hu Jintao
and Li Lanqing expressed their sympathy and condolences during
Lu's illness or after his death.
</P>
<P>
Lu took part in the Chinese revolution in 1937, and became a
member of the Chinese Communist Party in 1938.
</P>
<P>
He achieved outstanding military exploits during the war to
liberate China in the 1940s.
</P>
<P>
After 1949, he served in many positions, including secretary of
the CPC committees of Chongqing City and Sichuan Province, as well
as governor of the province.
</P>
<P>
He was a member of the 13th Central Advisory Commission.
</P>
