<HEADLINE> Aliens' Rights Protected in Chinese Law Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- In order to protect the rights
and interests of foreign enterprises and aliens in China and
promote China's opening up, people's courts must strictly abide by
international conventions, bilateral and multilateral pacts, and
civil procedure law in dealing with law cases involving aliens.
</P>
<P>
This comment was made by Zheng Gang, vice-president of the
Beijing Higher People's Court, here today.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, Beijing People's Courts at all levels
had altogether 9,882 unredeemed law cases by the end of this July,
involving a total of one billion yuan, among them some cases
involving aliens.
</P>
<P>
As a signatory to the "New York Convention", China has an
obligation to execute law cases involving aliens according to this
convention and other related pacts, Zheng explained.  
</P>
</TEXT>
