<HEADLINE> In-form China Best Prepared for Military Pentathlon Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The China's military
pentathlon team has been in the best form, ready to dominate this
week's CISM 46th Military Pentathlon Championships, China's team
official said here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Team leader Jiao Liming said: "We've been prepared for the
competition for a whole year and we are confident to dominate the
event at home."
</P>
<P>
A ten-member team, led by five world champions, is seeking to
sweep all the six titles, including the men's individual and
women's relay race trophies which they did not make last year in
Kristinehamn, Sweden.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team also won the men's team trophy, the Debrus
Cup, three times in row and Wang Lianying have taken the women's
individual title in four straight years.
</P>
<P>
"We've made a big improvement in the past year and could do
better this time," Jiao told reportor here two days before the
start of the seven-day military sport gala.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team had a four-month train this winter in a
plateau camp in Kunming, Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
"The veterans regained their best forms after the winter
training session, with some even making remarkable improvements,"
said Jiao. "Like Yang Chunyi and Guo Xinqiao, both 33, who
overpassed their own records in the cross-country race."
</P>
<P>
"It is hard to image they could make it at this age," Jiao
added.
</P>
<P>
The team attended two simulated competitions held by the
Chinese army in June and in August, and finished well in the two
rehearsals.
</P>
<P>
"The men's team surpassed their own winning record in Sweden
by 18 points in June," Jiao said.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jianzhu, coach of the Chinese women's team, said, "The four
women athletes improved by five seconds each in the 500 meters
relay race."
</P>
<P>
Jiao said they invited China's well-known sport psychologists
to the team, talig with the team members and the coaches, which
has been proved a big benefit for trainings.
</P>
<P>
"We're in the best form ever for the upcoming contest," Jiao
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
