<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The following are major
news items in leading U.S. newspapers on Tuesday:
</P>
<P>
The Washington Post:
</P>
<P>
-- With the investigation of President Bill Clinton becoming a
central concern for Congress this week, lawmakers have begun to
grapple with the question that independent counsel Kenneth W.
Starr's report will force them to confront: Do Clinton's actions
amount to impeachable offenses?
</P>
