by mountains and rivers, and that the peoples of the two nations
share a tradition of friendship.
</P>
<P>
Song Pong Hwan, charge d'affaires ad interim of the DPRK
Embassy in Beijing, said that the friendship between the peoples
of the DPRK and China was fostered by the older generation of
leaders. He said he believes that such a traditional friendship
will be furthered in the 21st century. 
