<HEADLINE> Floods Cause Heavy Damages to Education Sector in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- At least 10,000 educational
institutions in Bangladesh have been affected so far by the
current floods and damage to the education sector has been
estimated at 6.5 billion taka (138.3 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The government has appealed to the donor countries and other
development agencies for 3.4 billion taka (72.3 million dollars)
"flash aid" to recover from the immediate losses caused by the
nearly two-month-long devastating floods.
</P>
<P>
Eight thousand primary schools, 1,758 secondary schools and
colleges have been affected by floods, according to a primary
assessment conducted by the Education Ministry, BSS news agency
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the total affected-primary schools, 3,000 were fully damaged
and infrastructures of the rest were partially affected.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary assessment was made on the basis of reports
from the 47 flood-hit districts.
</P>
<P>
A full assessment of the damage to the education sector will be
made when the flood waters recede, Education Ministry sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Most of the schools and colleges in the country's central part
have been inundated by flood waters, and textbooks and other
classroom materials have been destroyed, the ministry sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The government will undertake immediate repairs on the basis of
existing preliminary damage estimates, and a massive re-equipping
program of the institutions will be taken in the affected
districts, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
