<HEADLINE> Clothes, Quilts Donated to Northeast Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Sufficient clothes and quilts
have been collected for flood victims in northeast China's
Nenjiang and Songhuajiang river basins, the Ministry of Civil
Affairs said here today.
</P>
<P>
Stricken by the worst flooding in decades, the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region and Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces in
northeast China suffered enormous losses in the past month.
</P>
<P>
Though the floods are now receding, many people who lost their
homes in the flooding face a bitter winter. So, a shortage of
thick clothes and quilts was an urgent problem in the flood-hit
areas.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Civil Affairs, which is in charge of disaster
relief, issued an urgent circular in late August, requiring
Beijing and Tianjin cities, and Hebei, Liaoning and Shandong
provinces to collect cotton clothes and quilts for the flood
victims in northeast China. The circular also required that the
work be done within 15 days.
</P>
<P>
Ministry officials said today that by September 6, over 38
million items of clothing and quilts, some 23 million of which
were cotton, had been raised in the five above-mentioned cities
and provinces.
</P>
<P>
Most of the clothes and quilts have already arrived in the
flood-hit areas, and the rest are on the way, according to the
officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
