<HEADLINE> Second SAARC Trade Fair Opens in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Second Trade Fair of the
South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation (SAARC) was
opened here Tuesday afternoon by SAARC Secretary General Naeem U.
Hasan.
</P>
<P>
At the opening ceremony, Sri Lankan Minister of Internal and
External Commerce K.T. Wickramaratne said the SAARC commerce
ministers when they last met in April this year formally decided
that Sri Lanka would host the SAARC Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
He said the fair was conceived as an integral part of the
economic cooperation policy within the region so as to give an
opportunity for businesses in the region to offer the products
that they have for export as well as to enhance their network and
form alliances among themselves.
</P>
<P>
The main purpose of the fair is to project the image of SAARC
member countries through the full range of their respective
economic activities to enhance economic cooperation and to promote
regional trade, investment and tourism, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
There are about 300 stalls at the exhibition from the seven
SAARC member countries -- Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives,
Nepal, Pakistan and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka has 136 stalls, India 70, Pakistan 48 and other four
countries have 20 stalls at the fair.
</P>
<P>
The first SAARC trade fair was held in 1996 in India. 
</P>
