<HEADLINE> China Charity Federation Receives Donations of 470 Million Yuan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The China Charity Federation
has received donations totaling 470 million yuan (about 57 million
U.S. dollars) since it began flood-relief activities last month,
an official of the Federation said at a press conference today.
</P>
<P>
Most of the donations have already been distributed to flood
victims, he said.
</P>
<P>
During the past 30 days, the Federation has collected 270
million yuan in cash and 200 million yuan worth of relief
materials and goods.
</P>
<P>
He added that so far 413 million yuan in cash and relief
goods has been sent to the flooded areas including Hunan,
Hubei and Jiangxi provinces.
</P>
<P>
Media reports said that the Federation has just received a
donation of three million yuan from Shanghai, which will be used
to set up a fund for those injured in the flood-fighting battles.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the Federation is also preparing a
fund to aid the anti-flood heroes.
</P>
<P>
Information about the fund and charity sales has already been
made available on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
During this summer, about 223 million people in 29 of China's
provinces and regions have suffered flood devastation. So far,
3,004 people have been killed and about five million houses
destroyed. Direct losses are estimated at more than 166 billion
yuan (about 20 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
At today's press conference, the China Charity Federation, the
All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, the All-China Youth
Federation, and other associations, jointly sponsored a program to
help flood victims rebuild their homes.
</P>
<P>
The China Charity Federation has designed two kinds of flood
relief commemorative envelopes for its program which will be
issued in the inland areas and the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
