<HEADLINE> Wu Yi on Measures to Ensure Economic Growth (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- State Councillor Wu Yi said
here today that the Chinese government will take more effective
measures to further expand domestic demand and open wider to the
outside world in a bid to ensure the fulfilment of this year's
economic growth target.
</P>
<P>
She told a symposium on the investment strategy of
multinational corporations which opened here today that the
measures will mainly focus on six aspects:
</P>
<P>
First, financial policies will be more vigorously resorted to
to raise more funds to increase investment in the badly-needed
infrastructure. More bank loans are also expected to support this
drive.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, more funds will be injected into science and
technology, and education.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government has the ability and conditions to do so
without incurring duplicated construction and triggering
inflation," she noted.
</P>
<P>
Second, the government has decided to increase the input in
irrigation and water conservancy and environmental protection and
accelerate the construction of a number of key projects covering
railways, highways, telecommunications, key airports, urban
construction, state-owned grain warehouses, rural power grids and
commercial housing.
</P>
</TEXT>
