<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Gets ADB Aid in Developing Private Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) approved Tuesday a 70 million U.S. dollars package of
assistance to accelerate the private sector development in Sri
Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The assistance consists of a Partial Credit Guarantee and Loan
in respect of a Credit Enhancement Facility (CEF) for Private
Enterprises, the Manila-based bank said in a press release.
</P>
<P>
The main objectives of the CEF are to provide Sri Lankan banks
access to international capital markets and channel long-term
funds from international investors to assist medium and large
private enterprises in capacity expansion and technology
upgrading.
</P>
<P>
It is anticipated that the combined resources of 70 million
dollars will generate investments of at least 250 million dollars
by assisting more than 100 private medium and large enterprises,
and possibly generate about 30,000 jobs. 
