<HEADLINE> DPR Korea Withdraws from Military Pentathlon Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's
Republic of Korea pulled out of this week's CISM 46th Military
Pentathlon World Championships,the organizing committee said
today.
</P>
<P>
The DPR Korea team, which scheduled to arrive here today, told
the committee yesterday through the Korean Embassy in China that
their pentathlon team is not available for the competition.
</P>
<P>
No reason have been given for their abrupt decision.
</P>
<P>
Jiao Liming, leader of the Chinese team, said after he heard
the news, "We're disappointed for their pull-out. They're the
biggest rivals for our women's team. We're well prepared and
also confident to beat them if they come here."
</P>
<P>
Wu Jianzhu, coach of the Chinese women's team, said, "It will
be easier to defend the women's team title without the challenge
from the Koreans."
</P>
<P>
China won both the team and individual titles in women's
division last year in Kristinehamn, Sweden, but lost the relay
race to DPR Korea.
</P>
<P>
The DPRK, which sent their first women's team to the event in
1995, defeated the Chinese women to win the team trophy, the
Challenge Cup,in 1996, and pocketed two silver team medals in the
other participations.
</P>
<P>
The Korean women also took every time the individual silver
and bronze medals,nevertheless, losing every time to China's
four-time champion Wang Lianying.
</P>
<P>
A total of 176 athletes from 24 countries will compete in the
annual military sport event, which is slated from September
10-16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
