<HEADLINE> Beijing Marks Birthday of Taiwan Studies Society </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Officials and scholars
gathered at the Great Hall of the People here today to mark the
10th anniversary of the Taiwan Studies Society.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Siyuan, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress and president of the society, said that
the non-governmental organization has helped increase exchanges
across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
The society was founded when tension between the two sides
relaxed in 1988, and exchanges started to increase.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 10 years, the society has received some 1,000
visitors from Taiwan, and sent many members to visit the island
province. It has completed more than 30 programs on Taiwan
studies.
</P>
<P>
At the moment the society has 800 members.
</P>
<P>
Chen Yunlin, director of the Taiwan Affairs Office of the State
Council, attended the celebration. 
