<HEADLINE> French Sports Minister Talks about Super League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
PARIS, September 8 (Xinhua) -- French sports minister
Marie-George Buffet said she was worried about plans for a
European soccer Super League at a time when she was working to
reduce the sports calendar to fight against doping.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in a press conference Tuesday, Buffet said that
"While we're trying to reduce the soccer calendar, there comes a
project which is going to increase the burden on athletes for
purely financial reasons."
</P>
<P>
The minister's remarks came as she was setting up a working
group of doctors and scholars who will have to publish a report
within two months following the doping scandal which rocked the
cycling Tour de France in July.
</P>
<P>
The group will study ways to reduce the sports calendar and
to preserve the independence of sports doctors, whom Buffet said
were torn between the demands of their employers and the need to
protect the health of athletes.
</P>
<P>
Buffet's antidoping bill will go before the French parliament
on November 18. 
</P>
