<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Broadly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed lower across the board Tuesday
on continued profit taking.
</P>
<P>
The market, which opened higher this morning, succumbed to
profit taking as players locked in their profits and saw the
100-quality stocks Composite Index (CI) fell 21.45 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the CI was 95.50 points lower at 349.56, the
all-share Emas Index eased 21.54 points to 94.01, the Industrial
Index declined 174.88 points to 686.38 and the second board index
shed 10.85 points to 95.0.
</P>
<P>
Losers overwhelmed gainers by 743 to 41, while 45 counters were
unchanged and 93 others untraded.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover shrunk to 609.854 million shares valued at
1.042 billion ringgit (274.27 million U.S. dollars) from 1.101
billion shares worth 1.576 billion ringgit (414.736 million U.S.
dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover fell to 579.552 million shares valued
at 991.774 million ringgit (260.993 million U.S. dollars) from
1.049 billion shares worth 1.497 billion ringgit (393.947 million
U.S. dollars) on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The second board index declined to 30.302 million shares valued
at 50.981 million ringgit (13.416 million U.S. dollars) from
Monday's 51.321 million shares worth 79.977 million ringgit
(21.046 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The off market turnover, however, reversed the trend to end
higher at 4.616 million shares valued at 5.238 million ringgit
(1.378 million U.S. dollars) from Monday's 3.455 million shares
worth 6.125 million ringgit (1.611 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
On sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 25.185
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
39.751 million shares, construction 78.058 million shares,
trade/services 181.229 million shares, infrastructures 1.356
million shares, finance 117.470 million shares, hotels 1.186
million shares, properties 48.050 million shares, plantation
14.257 million shares, mining 1.969 million shares, trusts 281,000
shares, closed/fund 251,000 shares and loans 70.508 million
shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
