<DOCNO> XIE19980908.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Fund Industry Sees Marginal Net Inflows in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's unit trust
industry recorded marginal net inflows of 3.5 million U.S. dollars
in July after a heavy outflow of 133.9 million U.S. dollars in
June.
</P>
<P>
Out of the 14 sectors, only five saw net inflows in the month,
according to the Hong Kong Investment Funds Association (HKIFA),
which groups 47 fund management firms.
</P>
<P>
For the second consecutive month, the six Asian sectors all
registered net outflows in July. However, net outflows from the
Asian sectors dropped substantially to 32 million U.S. dollars
from 141 million U.S. dollars in June.
</P>
<P>
Analyzing the sales of Asian funds, Lin Yoke Seetoh, acting
chairman of HKIFA, said: "As the outlook for the region continues
to be bleak, investors continue to stay away from Asian equity
funds. However, since July represented a relatively stable month
for the region, the level of redemption had subsided."
</P>
<P>
The month of July saw consistent robust inflows into European
equity funds, with net inflows, at 48.7 million U.S. dollars, the
highest recorded this year.
</P>
<P>
Investors have been turning to the more developed stock and
bond markets as the prospects of recovery for most Asian economies
appear distant, Seetoh remarked. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
