<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals to Macao Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals to Macao in the
first seven months in 1998 reached 4,008,457, down 6.8 percent
from the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Chinese tourists (including those from Hong Kong) accounted for
77.2 percent of the total, an increase of 4.9 percent over the
first seven months of 1997, according to figures released by the
Macao Statistics and Census Department on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, tourist arrivals from the Republic of Korea,
Japan, Southeast Asia, South Asia and America decreased 80.3
percent, 56.4 percent, 46.3 percent, 33.3 percent and 21 percent.
