<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Two successive bombs blew up
early morning on Tuesday in the downtown area of Macao, injuring
14 police and journalists with five seriously hurt, local media
reports said.
</P>
<P>
At about 1:20 a.m. local time, a bomb ripped off the rear part
of a red private car parking at a roadside. Receiving reports of
the explosion, police rushed to the site to conduct
investigations.
</P>
<P>
About one hour and 20 minutes later, another bomb planted in a
motorcycle nearby, which was supposed to be a time bomb, went off,
injuring four police men and 10 journalists.
</P>
<P>
Local officials vowed that police would spare no effort to
round up the troublemakers. 
</P>
