<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flower Center Forms In East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Zhangzhou City, known as the
home of the narcissus in east China's Fujian Province, has grown
into one of the country's largest flower cultivation centers.
</P>
<P>
The city now produces approximately 300 species of flowers,
with an annual output value of 300 million yuan (36 million US
dollars), three times that of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The city has favorable natural conditions for cultivating
flowers, and decided to develop the flower industry into a new
economic growth area three years ago.
</P>
<P>
The city also plans to build a flower-cultivating belt 50
kilometers by 0.6 kilometers along the Number 324 National Highway
by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Zhangzhou has now spent 42.1 million U.S. dollars for its
flower industry, and set up more than 60 enterprises to cultivate
such ornamental plants as lilies, roses, orchids and palm trees.
</P>
<P>
The city is currently building a wholesale flower market which
is scheduled to open in two years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
