<HEADLINE> Share Prices Inch Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Share prices inched up on
Singapore Stock Market Tuesday although sentiment was affected by
the decline on Kuala Lumpur stock market.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) went up 6.58 points to
end at 868.68 points after having surged up 57.06 points in the
trading Monday.
</P>
<P>
Brokers said Malaysia's 95-point drop which wiped out
Monday's hefty gains dampened sentiment here despite players took
profits after Monday's rally.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover declined to 182.82 million units valued at
210.47 million Singapore dollars (121.55 million U.S. dollars).
Losers outnumbered gainers by 146 to 60 with 350 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
KepLand remained the most active stock of the day with a volume
of 12.96 million stocks traded. It was followed by DBS Land that
had 11.60 million units done. TAC 200 was next with 9.72 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SIA 200 was the top gainer of the day as it gained 20 cents to
close at 5.25 Singapore dollars. HKL rose by 19 cents to finish at
1.05 U.S. dollars. Both Jar Mat and Venture w99 moved up 16 cents
and they ended 2.04 U.S. dollars and 3.68 Singapore dollars
respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH was the biggest loser of the day as it
shed by 60 cents to finish at 12.60 Singapore dollars. Creative 50
lost 50 cents to close at 18.00 Singapore dollars. C &AMP; C inched
down 24 cents to end at 2.18 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
