<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real IRA Declare Total Ceasefire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Real IRA, the terrorist
group that bombed Omagh in Northern Ireland last month, said on
Tuesday it was declaring a "complete" ceasefire starting from
Monday midnight.
</P>
<P>
The republican splinter group, which suspended its armed
activities three days after the Omagh blast that killed 29 people
on August 15, issued its ceasefire announcement to Ireland's
national broadcasting network RTE.
</P>
<P>
As a result of intense consultation that has taken place over
recent weeks, and in accordance with the constitution of the Real
IRA, the volunteers...have determined a complete cessation of all
military activity, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Irish Prime Minister Bertie Ahern was quoted in television
reports as saying the Real IRA statement was important and
positive for the Northern Ireland peace process provided it was
fully implemented.
</P>
<P>
But he made clear the British and Irish governments remained
determined to track down the Omagh bombers.
</P>
<P>
The Real IRA was formed by a small core of hard-liners who
stormed out of the IRA in late 1997 in protest against the
Northern Ireland peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Irish Republican Army (IRA), the mainstream republican
guerrilla force, declared a ceasefire in July 1997, which paved
the way for full-scale peace talks and led to the signing of the
historic peace agreement in last April. 
</P>
</TEXT>
