<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Spokesman on Foreign Minister Tang's Visit to US, Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan's upcoming visit to the United States will be helpful in
speeding the implementation of the wide-ranging unanimity reached
by leaders of both nations during their recent summit, and expand
the bilateral exchanges and cooperation in economy, trade,
science, education, energy, environmental protection, judiciary
and military fields.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao made this remark at a
routine news conference today. At the invitation of US Secretary
of State Madeleine Albright, Tang will pay an official visit to
the U.S. on September 27-29, after attending the United Nations
General Assembly, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
It will be his first visit to the U.S. as foreign minister, the
spokesman said, and the first visit to U.S. by a Chinese foreign
minister in the wake of the exchange of successful visits between
heads of state of the two nations.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister will hold talks with Albright, and
meet with other U.S. leaders. They will have an extensive and
profound exchange of views on Sino-U.S. relations and important
international and regional issues of mutual concern, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said he believed that the visit will also be conducive to
China and the US' efforts to build a constructive, strategic
partnership facing the 21st century, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he announced that Tang Jiaxuan will also pay an
official visit to Canada from September 30 to October 5 as guest
of his Canadian counterpart Hon Lloyd Axworthy.
</P>
<P>
The visit, first to be paid by a foreign minister of the new
Chinese government, would produce a significant impact on the
Sino-Canadian friendship and cooperative ties, he said.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that Tang will meet with the Canadian prime
minister and parliament leaders, and confer with his Canadian
counterpart Axworthy during the visit.
</P>
<P>
The two sides would discuss the further implementation of the
strategy to build an overall Sino-Canadian cooperative partnership
oriented to the 21st century, reached when President Jiang Zemin
visited Canada last year, Zhu said, adding that they would also
exchange views on international and regional issues of common
concern.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Canada, Tang will also attend the opening
ceremony of the Chinese Consulate General in Calgary, Zhu said.
</P>
