<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Demands Viet Nam to Withdraw From Submerged Reefs in Nansha </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China has made serious
representations to the Vietnamese side, strongly demanding it to
withdraw from two of China's submerged reefs which was unlawfully
occupied by the Vietnamese navy, said Chinese Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Zhu Bangzao.
</P>
<P>
Zhu made the remarks at a regular press conference here this
afternoon, when asked to comment on the fact that the Vietnamese
navy recently sent warships, suddenly occupying and setting up
permanent facilities on Aonan and Jindun submerged reefs to the
southeast of Nanhuitan of China's Nansha Archipelago.
</P>
<P>
It is known to all that the Nansha archipelago has been a part
of Chinese territory since ancient times, Zhu said, adding that
China has the indisputable sovereignty over the Nansha
archipelago and its adjacent waters.
</P>
<P>
The fact that the Vietnamese side recently occupied the
above-mentioned two submerged reefs by force has seriously
infringed upon China's territory and sovereignty, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
China has strongly demanded the Vietnamese side to withdraw
from the two reefs at once, dismantle all the facilities which
were illegally established there and guarantee that such acts of
occupation would never happen again, the spokesman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
