<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank Allocates Two Million Yuan to Aid Poor Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Construction Bank of China
(CBC) announced here today that it has allocated two million yuan
to aid college students from the flooded areas who are having
difficulties financing their college education.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the CBC said that more than 1,400 poor students in
86 colleges and universities, including Beijing and Qinghua
universities, will be aided with the funds.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the bank said that the CBC has so far donated
over 23 mllion yuan to the Yangtze River Valley and the Nenjiang
River Valley, both heavily hit by devastating floods this summer.
</P>
<P>
Since 1996, the CBC has allocated 2 million yuan each year to
aid more than 1,000 needy college students, the spokesman said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
