<HEADLINE> Mandela to Visit North America--Newspaper </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- South African President
Nelson Mandela will embark on an extensive North American tour
next week, The Star daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Highlights include an address to the United Nations General
Assembly, receiving the United States' highest civilian honor,
and a state visit to Canada.
</P>
<P>
South African, American and Canadian officials said at the
weekend that Mandela will arrive in New York on September 15 for
a seven-day official visit before proceeding to Canada on
September 23.
</P>
<P>
Mandela is expected to hold meetings with heads of state
attending the U.N. General Assembly's opening session, said the
paper.
</P>
<P>
In Washington, Mandela will meet U.S. President Bill Clinton
and lawmakers, and receive the Congressional Gold Medal. 
</P>
