<BODY>
<HEADLINE> FM Spokesman on Macao, Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China hopes the Portuguese
Macao authorities carry out their administrative responsibilities
earnestly and take further and effective steps to maintain good
order in Macao, a Foreign Ministry spokesman said here today.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Bangzao said at the weekly press conference that by so
doing, social stability, economic development, and a smooth
transition and transfer of power can be guaranteed in Macao.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side attaches great importance to social order in
Macao," the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese government will, as always, render
support and cooperation to the Portuguese side in its efforts to
safeguard social security and order in Macao.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of Taiwan, Zhu stated that political negotiations
have historically been put on the agenda between the two sides of
the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Through the concerted efforts of the two sides, he continued,
contacts and economic and cultural exchanges across the straits
continue to maintain a growing momentum.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that common ground has been reached on the issue of
"One China" with compatriots across the straits, a concept which
has also acquired world recognition.
</P>
<P>
China's sovereignty and territorial integrity can by no means
be split, Zhu said, adding that if the Taiwan authorities are
sincere they should break away from their stance of "Two Chinas,"
and thus will have no reason to put off procedural talks on
political negotiations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
