<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Agreement Reached on Teachers' Wage Rise in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Israel's teachers union and
the Finance Ministry have reached an agreement on wage increase
following overnight marathon negotiations, the Jerusalem Post
daily reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement has paved the way for the schools to open in the
day after a one-week delay due to teachers' strike for wage rise.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, teachers will get an overall 1.9 percent
real wage increase and additional payments for accompanying school
trips.
</P>
<P>
Principals and teachers performing administrative duties will
receive a 25-percent pay increase.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also includes funds for the long school day and
special programs for gifted and needy pupils.
</P>
<P>
The teachers union launched the strike last Tuesday, keeping
1.2 million students out of school. 
</P>
</TEXT>
