<HEADLINE> Cambodian Protesters Dispersed by Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian police dispersed
with water cannons and batons thousands of demonstrators
protesting outside the National Assembly (parliament) Tuesday
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Several hundred policemen blocked a park that the demonstrators
called "Democracy Square" and removed tents and makeshift shelters
in the park.
</P>
<P>
Police fired into the sky to scare away the protesters.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, under the protection U.N. staffs, Sam Rainsy, leader
of the main opposition Sam Rainsy Party, Tuesday morning left the
office of Lakhan Mehrotra, U.N. Secretary General's special
representative to Cambodia, for a meeting with Prince Norodom
Ranariddh at Ranariddh's residence.
</P>
<P>
He was reported to have returned before noon to Mehrotra's
office in Cambodiana Hotel for a meeting with a group of
ambassadors.
</P>
<P>
Second Prime Minister Hun Sen and the government had issued a
warrant to arrest Sam Rainsy but canceled it after Mehrotra
consulted with Hun Sen and co-Interior Minister Sar Kheng.
</P>
<P>
Tension grew all day as the government ordered the
demonstrators to leave the protest locations before Monday
midnight. 
</P>
</TEXT>
