<HEADLINE> China Values Cooperation with UN Human Rights Office, FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government hopes
the visit here of Mary Robinson, the United Nation's high
commissioner for human rights, will enhance mutual understanding
and strengthen cooperation, Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao
said at his regular press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
China values Mary Robinson's visit, scheduled for September 6
to 15 at the invitation of the Chinese government, Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
He also announced that Chinese leaders will meet with the
visitor and her party.
</P>
<P>
Assistant Foreign Minister Wang Guangya held talks with Madame
Robinson yesterday morning and the two signed a memorandum of
intent on cooperation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The visitors then attended a symposium of the Chinese Academy
of Social Sciences law department on the Two UN Covenants on Human
Rights yesterday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Ms. Robinson will hold talks with Chinese government officials
at various levels, non-governmental organizations, and scholarly
institutions, Zhu noted, adding that the UN official will also
visit Tibet and Shanghai. 
