<DOCNO> XIE19980908.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qingdao Invests More in Housing Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- This major port city of east
China's Shandong Province has significantly increased investment
in residential housing construction this year.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao's total investment in housing construction jumped 50
percent on a yearly basis in the first six months this year, and
floor space sold during this period more than doubled, according
to local official figures.
</P>
<P>
Official estimates project Qingdao's investment in residential
housing construction at 3.1 billion yuan for the whole of 1998.
</P>
<P>
In the remaining four months of this year, Qingdao will start
constructing another 1.77 million square meters of economical
residential housing, with investment budgeted at 840 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Qingdao constructed 13.16 million square meters of residential
housing between 1992 and 1997, with a total investment of 15.2
billion yuan for the five-year period.
</P>
<P>
The construction boom has helped raise Qingdao's per capita
housing area for urban residents from 6.6 square meters in the
early 1990s to a present 8.8 square meters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
