<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue Surging in Tokyo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices continued surging in
Tokyo Tuesday, driven by a rise in Nikkei index futures prices.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange closed at 14,913.49, up 123.43
points, or 0.83 percent, after posting a 5.32 percent gain Monday.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering all
First Section issues, dropped 1.64 points, or 0.14 percent, from
Monday's close to end at 1,131.01.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the main section came to an estimated 500 million
shares, little changed from Monday.
</P>
<P>
Failed Toa Steel Co., a major electric-furnace steelmaker, was
the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
The market experienced sharp fluctuation throughout the day. At one
point, the Nikkei soared more than 500 points and returned to the
15,000 level for the first time intraday since August 26. Investors
then sold to take profits.
</P>
<P>
An hour into trading, the Osaka Nikkei index futures market sprang
to life. The price of the September contract rocketed as high as
15,310 before falling back to end at 14,870, down 60 points from
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei cash index essentially tracked the same course. It hit
a session high 15,294.26 before investors whittled away at the gains
throughout the rest of the day.
</P>
<P>
Monday's 747-point rise, the Nikkei's second biggest point gain
this year, was also driven by high-flying futures prices.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,341 issues listed on the First Section, gainers surpassed
losers 612 to 523, with 165 issues remaining unchanged.
</P>
</TEXT>
