<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Enterprise Groups Report Sound Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Enterprise groups have
developed rapidly in Shanghai, becoming a leading economic pillar
of this metropolis of more than 12 million people.
</P>
<P>
Last year, Shanghai's 181 enterprise groups accounted for 67
percent of the city's total industrial sales, 48 percent of retail
sales, and 22 percent of real estate sales, according to official
statistics.
</P>
<P>
The enterprise groups had an average of three billion yuan (362
million US dollars) business revenue last year, with asset value
averaging at 5.2 billion yuan (626 million US dollars). Seventy of
the groups had profits valued at 50 million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
Altogether, the enterprise groups had 42.6 billion yuan (5.13
billion US dollars) of gross income last year, and their average
assets-to-liabilities ratio stood at 59 percent, down 2 percentage
points from 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
