<HEADLINE> PTA Re Registers Fast Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- PTA Re, the reinsurance
company of the Common Market for East and South African (COMESA)
states recorded a 33.3 percent growth in the volume of premiums
underwritten in 1997, the annual report and accounts show.
</P>
<P>
The regional reinsurance company wrote a premium of 513.37
million Shillings (8.63 million U.S. Dollars) last year compared
to 384.54 million Shillings in 1996, the Daily Nation newspaper
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Earned premium for the the year amounted to 331.1 million
Shillings compared to 191.47 million Shillings in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The financial statement shows that the company made a net
profit of 10.05 million Shillings compared to a 20.54 million
Shillings loss in 1996.
</P>
<P>
During the year, the paid-up share capital rose to 380.22
million Shillings from 357.82 million Shillings.
</P>
<P>
The company currently has 20 shareholders mainly insurance and
reinsurance firms from the COMESA region and the PTA Bank.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Reinsurance Corporation is the major shareholder with a
commensurate voting power of 43.08 percent. 
</P>
