<HEADLINE> Vietnam Deplores Hatred for Ethnic Vietnamese in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's foreign ministry
released a statement Tuesday, accusing some Cambodian forces of
instigating hatred for ethnic Vietnamese in the country.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that a number of extremist elements in
Cambodia, driven by "political ambitions," have incited hatred for
ethnic Vietnamese in Cambodia and intimidated or killed aliens
there.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese government and people "vehemently protest these
barbarous acts taken by a number of extremist elements which
seriously violate human rights.
</P>
<P>
Such acts have further complicated the situation in Cambodia,
undermined the friendship between Vietnam and Cambodia, and
poisoned the atmosphere of peace, cooperation and development in
Southeast Asia, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam urged Cambodian King Norodom Sihanouk, with his
prestige and influence, to prevent the recurrence of "such
racialist crimes against ethnic Vietnamese."
</P>
<P>
It also requested the Cambodian government to take effective
measures to stop the crimes and guarantee the safety of life and
property of ethnic Vietnamese in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the current situation in Cambodia, Vietnam hoped
that a new Cambodian government should be established soon to
stabilize the situation and realize the Cambodian people's
aspirations for peace and development, the statement added.
</P>
