<HEADLINE> Tanzania Issues Stamps on Children's Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania Tuesday
launched a set of four stamps on children's rights.
</P>
<P>
The stamps, with a total face value of 1,300 Shillings (about
two U.S. Dollars), were jointly launched by the Tanzania Posts
Corporation (TPC) and the Kulea Center for Children's Rights, a
non-governmental organization (NGO).
</P>
<P>
The stamps include "girls and boys have equal rights" with a
face value of 150 Shillings, "children have rights to education,"
250 Shillings, "children have rights not to be beaten," 400
Shillings, and "children have the right to be loved," 500
Shillings.
</P>
<P>
The stamps are being launched as one way of fulfilling the
commitment of the United Nations Convention on the Rights of
Children, a joint statement by TPC and the NGO said.
</P>
<P>
It noted that the stamps will reach hundreds of thousands of
people both in Tanzania and abroad, and will help communicate the
messages on children's rights. 
