<HEADLINE> Exports from Hebei Development Zones Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Exports from 21 development
zones in north China's Hebei Province maintained a rising momentum in
the first half of this year despite of impact of the Asian
financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Hebei has 19 development zones and two state-level high-tech
development zones, which serve as the leading foreign trade
contributors in this coastal province.
</P>
<P>
Their combined import and export value totaled 300 million
U.S. dollars in the first six months, up 16.7 percent over the
same period last year. Exports soared 35 percent to 200 million
U.S. dollars, said Shi Rongyao, a provincial trade official.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months of this year, these development zones
signed 1,158 foreign-funded contracts, involving foreign
investments of 2 billion U.S. dollars, one-third of
the province's total.
</P>
<P>
Since the provincial government readjusted its foreign trade
policy at the beginning of the year, exports to the European Union
increased by 13 percent and those to the United States rose 29
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
