<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Re Profit Down Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 8 (Xinhua) --Kenya Reinsurance Corporation
(KRC), whose privatization started last week, has released its
annual report and accounts for 1997 showing a slight decrease in
profit before taxation.
</P>
<P>
KRC Chairman Andrew Omanga was quoted by Tuesday's national
newspaper as saying that the general economic depression Kenya
experienced last year brought down the firm's pre-tax profit to
170.7 million Shillings (2.87 million U.S. Dollars) from 172.9
million Shillings in 1996.
</P>
<P>
While the world economy continued to expand, he said, Kenya's
performance was dismal at a 2.3 percent growth in 1997.
</P>
<P>
In 1997 the company's operating profit before working capital
charges was 689.2 million Shillings, up from 554.6 million
Shillings in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Omanga said the corporation's core business continued to be
reinsurance which recorded an underwriting loss of 253.3 million
Shillings compared with 282.9 million Shillings in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The report shows that the corporation's income from investment
amounted to 424 million Shillings, down from 455.9 million
Shillings in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The chairman said that the marginal decline in investment
income was mainly due to a decrease in short term investable
funds following substantial disbursements toward long term
assets.
</P>
<P>
The firm's privatization process started Monday last week the
search for strategic investors to take up part of the
shareholding before the rest of the shares are floated through
the Nairobi Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Omanga said that during the year, the corporation concentrated
on developing strategic relationship with key local business
partners while significant attention was also given to the
African region.
</P>
<P>
On future prospects, the chairman said that the corporation
plans to embrace the opportunities offered by the new information
technology which would enable it to exploit the market
opportunities for the benefit of the shareholders. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
