been withdrawn from the Turkish markets for fear that the current
Russian financial crisis would make a negative impact on Turkey's
economy.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's foreign currency reserve stood at 26.70 billion
dollars in June but fell to 21.96 billion at the end of last month.
