<HEADLINE> China Develops Digital High Definition Television System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 8 (Xinhua) -- China claimed today that it
has developed a prototype digital high definition television
(HDTV) system to become the fourth country in the world to possess
a self-developed HDTV ground broadcasting system.
</P>
<P>
Song Jian, head of the state major high-tech engineering
program said the digital HDTV system today began a five-day ground
broadcasting and receiving demonstration via the Central
Television Tower in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a news conference today, Song, also president of
Chinese Academy of Engineering, said China will begin trial
broadcasting of HDTV programs in around two years, and establish a
number of HDTV ventures.
</P>
<P>
The official said research has paved the way for China
to upgrade its television industry.
</P>
<P>
The research program, absorbing 15 million yuan (1.8 million
U.S dollars) of investment, was completed by more than 200
scientists from nine universities and research institutions after
two years of work.
</P>
<P>
The research units include Shanghai Jiaotong University,
Tianjin University and the Academy of Electronics Science. Most of
the research group leaders are scientists under 35 years old.
</P>
<P>
China is a big television producing country and Chinese
households have 300 million television sets. About 43 percent of
the output value of the country's electronics and information
industries comes from production of television sets, their related
electronics components and recording devices.  
</P>
</TEXT>
