in Durban, South Africa, Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina was quoted
as telling the parliament on Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The 7th parliament began its 10th session Monday afternoon and
is expected to be prorogued Tuesday due to the prolonged
devastating flood situation in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to convention, Bangladesh would be the next chairman
of the forum representing all non-aligned countries in the world,
the prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela was elected new NAM
chairman at its 12th summit held on September 2 and 3.
</P>
<P>
Hasina didn't attend the summit because of the floods in the
country. 
</P>
