<HEADLINE> Italy, Iran Seek Closer Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 7 (Xinhua) -- Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi
said here on Monday that the development of economic cooperation
between Italy and Iran was important to both countries.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with visiting Iranian Minister of Mines and Metals
Eshaq Jahangiri, Prodi said the economic cooperation between Italy
and Iran could play a positive role in maintaining regional peace
and stability.
</P>
<P>
A statement from the Prime Minister's Office said that during
the meeting, a message from Iranian President Khatami was sent to
Prodi. It asked Italy to continue to pay close attention to the
fate of Iranian citizens captured in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Prodi said that Italy is greatly concerned about the incident
and Rome was ready to contribute in any way possible to the
resolution. He also urged Iran "to continue to demonstrate its
moderation and thus avoid the crisis (between the two
nations) deteriorates further".
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of reinforcing bilateral cooperation
"in the open and constructive framework of cooperation which has
had positive effects in favor of peace and cooperation in our
respective geographic areas".
</P>
<P>
Prodi also met with visiting Iranian Foreign Trade Minister
Augusto Fantozzi later in the day. 
</P>
