<HEADLINE> Samsung's New Picture-Tube Joint Venture in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin-Samsung Display
Device Co. Ltd., a new joint venture between Tianjin Electronic
Meters Corporation and Samsung Display Device Corporation, began
formal production recently.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture is capable of producing large-screen and
high-definition color picture tubes. By the end of this year,
it is expected to be able to produce 300,000 units.
</P>
<P>
The jointly invested company is located in the Wuqing
Development Zone in suburban Tianjin, and has an area of 220,000
square meters.
</P>
<P>
Some 383 million U.S. dollars were spent for first-phase
building of the joint venture, most of which was used to finance
construction of two production lines -- one for producing color
picture tubes for TV sets and the other for computers. The TV
color picture-tube production line became operational recently.
</P>
<P>
The computer color picture-tube production line, with a
designed annual production capacity of 1.8 million units, has
just finished equipment installation and will begin production
early next year.
</P>
<P>
When both production lines become operational next year, the
company will be able to generate four billion yuan (481 million
U.S. dollars) in output value, said a company executive.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin is a major north China city for investment from the
Republic of Korea (ROK). So far, more than 700 projects, with
investments exceeding one-billion U.S. dollars, have been started
by investors from the ROK. The Samsung Group, for example, has
six joint ventures or solely invested businesses in
Tianjin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
