<HEADLINE> Italy Car Registrations Plummet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Italian car industry saw a
sharp decline in sales in August, according to statistics from the
Italian transport ministry on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said car registration plummeted by 11.43 percent
in August compared to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
In July, as car buyers scrambled to make purchases,
registration volume rose 3.15 percent, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
