<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Summer-Grain Reaches Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 8 (Xinhua) -- The output of summer grain
reached a record high this year in south China's Guangdong
Province with a harvest of over 9 million tons, an increase of
52,800 tons over 1997.
</P>
<P>
A provincial agricultural department official said the province
has achieved increasing output for five consecutive years. He told
that the output per mu (15 mu equals one hectare) reached 4.03
kilograms, one kilogram higher than the record 1997, and the sown
area of summer grain was about 1.5 million hectares, up 2,900
hectares.
</P>
<P>
He attributed this harvest to increased agriculture investment
which has ensured production despite some areas being hit by
floods. 
</P>
