<HEADLINE> High-Tech Industry Flourishing in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen, one of China's five
Special Economic Zones, in Guangdong Province, installed a series
of favorable policies on funding, land and taxes at the beginning
of this year to encourage the development of high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
A city government official said that the output value of
high-tech products was 39.9 billion yuan (4.8 billion
U.S. dollars) during the January-August period, up 35 percent over
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The output of program-controlled switchboards in Shenzhen
accounts for over 30 percent of China's total. In the first eight
months, Shenzhen produced 9.2 million units of program-controlled
switchboards, up 152 percent over the same 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, foreign companies such as
Epson and Du Pont have increased investment in Shenzhen, and
several large domestic high-tech enterprises including Founder
have established branches in Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this year, high-tech industry output value is
expected to account for 39 percent of the total industrial output
value of Shenzhen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
