<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Businesses Blooming in Northwest China Ethnic Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region began making efforts this year to develop
private businesses.
</P>
<P>
A regional government official said that by the end of July,
Ningxia had 92,000 private businesses, employing 180,000 people,
up 11 percent and 18 percent respectively year-on-year. Its
registered capital reached three billion yuan, with sales revenues
exceeding 3.1 billion yuan, up 22 percent, and 18 percent
respectively .
</P>
<P>
Beginning in 1990, local government has issued a series of
policies in terms of granting loans and raising capitals in favor
of the development of private businesses. Now the private sector
in Ningxia are engaged in a range of businesses, including
transportation, storage, real estate, and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
The total number of private enterprises reached 378 with over
one-million yuan in registered capital, and four of them are
listed among the country's top 500 private businesses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
