<HEADLINE> Insurance in Czech Rises by 20 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Insurance in the Czech Republic
totalled 31.7 billion korun (about 10.6 billion U.S. dollars) in
the first half of this year, marking a 20 percent increase over
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Insurance Company has said that compared with the
period of January-June 1997, life insurance rose by 16 percent to
7.2 billion korun (about 2.4 billion dollars) and other insurance
went up 25 percent to 24.5 billion korun (8.17 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
There are 36 insurance companies in the country, including
eight foreign ones. Insurance has become an important sector in
the Czech economic development. 
</P>
