<HEADLINE> Two Czech Men Stay in Car for 86 days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Two Czech men have set a
Guinness record by living in car for 86 days.
</P>
<P>
The old Guinness record was set not long ago by a German who
stayed in an OPEL car for 83.5 days.
</P>
<P>
Mrroslav Stepnicka, 31, and Michal Svoboda, 24, began their
record-breaking effort in two Skoda cars on June 13. They are
still in them.
</P>
<P>
Doctors, who conducted regular physical examinations on them,
said they are in good physical and mental conditions.
</P>
<P>
Mrroslav Stepnicka, a software designer, plans to stay in the
car for 120 days. A newspaper picture showing him working with a
computer in the car indicates no signs of tiredness.
</P>
<P>
He said he was happy there. His relatives and friends visited
him from time to time. They even celebrated his wedding
anniversary in the car last Thursday. 
</P>
