<HEADLINE> Kim Il Chol Appointed as Minister of People's Armed Forces </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Kim Il Chol has been
appointed minister of the People's Armed Forces of the Democratic
People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), the radio here reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The position had remained vacant since the former minister Choe
Gwang died in February, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Vice Marshal Kim Il Chol was appointed according to a decree
issued by Kim Jong Il, who was re-elected as the chairman of the
National Defense Commission (NDC) at the first session of the
tenth Supreme People's Assembly on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kim Il Chol, former first vice-minister of the People's Armed
Forces, was named as vice-chairman of the NDC at the assembly.
</P>
</TEXT>
