<HEADLINE> Survey: Brazil and Mexico, Two Reliable Countries to Invest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Brazil and Mexico are two
of the most reliable countries in Latin America to do business
with and to invest in, according to a new survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey of 150 trans-national companies was carried out by
the American Advisory Company A.T. Kearny. The results were
published Monday by Mexican newspaper Gazetta Mercantil
Latinoamericana.
</P>
<P>
The study was conducted from February to April after the Asian
financial crisis erupted. It highlighted the 10 most ideal
countries for investment. They were the United States, Brazil,
China, Britain, India, Germany, Mexico, Poland, Italy and Spain.
</P>
<P>
The survey showed that Argentina ranked 11th, while Chile
ranked 23rd. 
</P>
</TEXT>
