<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dengue Fever Kills 168 People in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 8 (Xinhua) -- Dengue fever has downed at
least 10,923 people and killed 168 nationwide so far this year,
Manila Bulletin reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Health Department officials as saying the
outbreaks have recently occurred in many areas across the country,
but there are no ongoing outbreaks in the 14 cities and
municipalities in Metro Manila.
</P>
<P>
On a national scale, the number of dengue fever cases is still
within the expected range, outgoing Health Secretary Felipe
Estrella said Monday.
</P>
<P>
He assured that all hospitals under the Department of Health
have been ready to admit an increased number of patients, saying
dengue fever express lanes and operations centers have been set up
to properly screen cases for referral to the hospitals.
</P>
<P>
A dengue information, education and communications campaign is
also being intensified in all regions, highlighting preventive
measures and proper case management, he said.
</P>
<P>
Estrella added that technical assistance, including
augmentation of medical supplies, is also being provided to local
government units and that a total of 8.8 million pesos (some
204,651 U.S. dollars) has been allotted to regional health offices
and hospitals for procurement of drugs and other supplies needed.
</P>
<P>
Estrella submitted his letter of resignation to President
Joseph Estrada on August 23. Estrada said he will appoint a new
health chief this week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
