<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Coasts into U.S. Open Quarterfinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Pete Sampras gave
talented Russian teenager Marat Safin a straight-set clinic today
and moved into a possible quarterfinal showdown with fellow
American Andre Agassi at the U.S. Open tennis championships.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Safin has been labeled a can't-miss star of
the future but he was no match for the top player of the present
today as Sampras cruised to a 6-4, 6-3, 6-2 victory.
</P>
<P>
Sampras registered 18 aces, including three in a row to end
the match, and faced only two break points in the 77-minute match
that was delayed by rain for more than two hours early in the
second set.
</P>
<P>
In the quarterfinals, Sampras will play the winner of today's
fourth-round between Agassi, the eighth seed, and ninth seed
Karol Kucera of Slovakia. Agassi has beaten Sampras in two of
three meetings this year.
</P>
<P>
Sampras closed out the match in spectacular fashion. After
falling behind 30-40, he unleashed three consecutive aces as
Safin simply shook his head in awe.
</P>
<P>
A winner of five Wimbledon and two Australian Open
titles,Sampras is seeking his fifth U.S. Open championship to tie
former Australian star Roy Emerson's record for Career Grand Slam
titles.Sampras also is attempting to tie fellow American Jimmy
Connor's modern day record of five U.S. Open titles.
</P>
<P>
Sampras earned his 600 career victory against just 162
losses.He is 152-26 in Grand Slam matches to lead all active
players and his 51-6 record at the Open is the best among active
players.
</P>
<P>
Sampras withstood an early barrage by Safin as he broke to go
up 5-4 and served out the first set. Following a two-hour rain
delay with Sampras leading 2-1 in the second set, the American
broke to go up 4-2 and served out the set.
</P>
<P>
In the final set, Sampras broke Safin to take 3-2 and broke
again to lead 5-2 before taking the match with three consecutive
aces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
