<HEADLINE> Williams Beats Pierce in U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Venus Williams of the United
States displayed her power and speed here this afternoon to beat
never-say-die Mary Pierce of France in the U.S. Open tennis
championships.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old fifth seed took the first set 6-1 easily, but
met strong challenge from the French 12th seed. After battling
5-all, Williams edged Pierce 6-5 in the second set following a
tough
11th game which saw eight deuce and 10 break points after 40-40.
</P>
<P>
Williams, who was aggressive throughout, returned the second
serves wide four times when she was facing tiebreaks. The two
players made a lot of unforced errors during the
last-point-battle.
It was a powerful match between two great players. Williams, the
lost finalist last year here, showed her potential today. She is
the fifth-ranked player in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
