<HEADLINE> Swedish Players Doing Good in U.S. Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Swedish players very quietly
are becoming a major factor at this year's U.S. Open tennis
championships.
</P>
<P>
Magnus Larsson's victory over second seed Marcelo Rios of
Chile Sunday night sent three Swedish players into the round of
16 at the U.S. Open for the first time since 1987. Earlier, Jonas
Bjorkman and Thomas Johansson had earned fourth round berths.
</P>
<P>
At least two Swedes have reached the round of 16 for the third
consecutive year at the Open. Bjorkman and Larsson also reached
the round of 16 last year and eventually both made it to the
quarterfinals. The last Swede to win the U.S. Open was Stefan
Edbergy in 1992 as he completed back-to-back titles.
</P>
<P>
In 1987, four Swedes -- Edberg, Mats Wilander, Anders Jarryd
and Jonas Svensson -- made the round of 16 in the Open. 
</P>
</TEXT>
