<HEADLINE> FILA Changes Regulation on Match Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The International Federation
of Associated Wrestling (FILA) announced on Monday to change
wrestling match time from present five minutes to two rounds of
three minutes.
</P>
<P>
According to the Iranian official news agency IRNA, the FILA
made the decision in its annual meeting held here on Monday upon
the demands of several members.
</P>
<P>
The new decision, which will take effect as of the beginning
of 1999, stipulates that wrestling match will be carried out in
two rounds of three minutes with a break of 30 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Many coaches have complained that they can not play an
important role in wrestling matches according to the present
regulation, as they can not contact with their wrestlers during
the matches, a FILA official said.
</P>
<P>
However, the new rule allows coaches to give necessary
instructions to wrestlers during the 30-second break between the
two rounds of match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
