<HEADLINE> Peruvian President Visits Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 7 (Xinhua) -- The Peruvian President
Alberto Fujimori Monday evening arrived here on a two-day official
visit to Romania. This is the first visit ever paid to Romania by
an incumbent Peruvian president.
</P>
<P>
"We will exploit every possibility to find ways for a more
fertile exchange between our two countries in all fields,
especially in the economic and commercial ones. I hope that my
visit will contribute to an even better understanding between our
two countries," Fujimori told the press upon his arrival at
Otopeni International Airport.
</P>
<P>
The agenda of President Fujimori's visit includes a meeting
with President Emil Constantinescu, Prime Minister Radu Vasile and
with the presidents of the two Chambers of Parliament. The
Peruvian president will also participate in a conference with the
Romanian businessmen in the Latin American House.
</P>
<P>
Among the most important topics to be discussed during the
visit are the identification of new areas of bilateral
cooperation, the development of trade and the possibility of
setting up joint ventures in domains of common interest. A series
of cooperation accords, in the field of tourism, the fight against
drug trafficking and in the cultural and scientific domain, are
expected to be signed during the visit.
</P>
<P>
Romania and Peru established the diplomatic relations in 1939.
The bilateral relations have been increasing over the last years,
but the total volume of trade amounts to a modest 10 million U.S.
dollars.  
</P>
