<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-08 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eritrea Eyes Uganda's Leather Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- A trade delegation from Eritrea
has said it intends to establish a trading house of leather products
in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
It will also establish other business contacts with its
Ugandan counterparts, Radio Uganda said Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
Raphael Ochan, the permanent secretary in the Ministry of
Tourism, Trade and Industry, met the delegation Monday morning
and briefed the Eritrean businessmen on his country's trade
policy.
</P>
<P>
The liberalization of trade and business policy in the country
has opened doors to international and local investors to
establish industries and other trade links, he said.
</P>
<P>
Alem Tseheye, who headed the delegation, told the Ugandan
official that they intend to do business with Ugandans who are
dealing in raw hides and leather products with the view to obtain
raw hides supply and the market for their products here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
