<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 3,700 Somali Refugees Return Home from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Some 3,738 Somali
refugees have been repatriated to their homeland from the Teferi
Ber Camp in Ethiopia's eastern Somali region.
</P>
<P>
Head of the Somali Region Refugees and Returnee Coordination
Office, Tsegaye Mihretu, said that the refugees who were back
home on August 26 and September 7 are among the 10,000 in the
camp who volunteered to leave, the Ethiopian News Agency reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
About 30,000 Somali refugees sheltered in nine refugee camps
of eastern Ethiopia have been repatriated to their motherland
since the repatriation started last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
