<HEADLINE> Congo Peace Talks Over, Accord to Be Signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 7 (Xinhua) -- Peace talks aimed at
ending the civil war in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC)
was over in Victoria Falls, Zimbabwe later Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the summit, Zambian President Frederick Chiluba,
announced that an agreement would be signed at 9 a.m. (0700 GMT)
Tuesday morning, South African national TV (SABC) reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, fighting in the DRC continued as an Angolan war
plane attacked the southeastern town of Kalemie, killing 25
people and wounding 40 others, SABC quoted a rebel officer as
saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
